    {
      "id": "5a93c517_75d611c5",
      "file_path": "src/main/java/org/onap/sdc/toscaparser/api/NodeTemplate.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 427,
      "message": "Not really. In this case while fetching nativeInterfaceDetails, I am fetching entire object where key is InterfaceDef.LIFECYCLE and not the value of this key from the map.\n\nBoth native and custom interface details are maps where keys are their interface names and the values are interface definition. Here is the sample output with existing code base;\n\ncustomInterfaceDetails -> {cxVNF1={type=org.openecomp.interfaces.node.lifecycle.CxVnf1, instantiate={description=operation description 1, implementation=Artifacts\\org.openecomp.resource.vf.CxVnf1\\org.openecomp.interfaces.node.lifecycle.CxVnf1\\Deployment\\Workflows\\BPMN\\instantiate.bpmn, inputs={oamip=null, type=string, default={get_property=[SELF, vlc1-oam-ip]}}}, upgrade={inputs={ipv4=null, type=string, default={get_property=[SELF, ipaddress]}}}}}\n\nnativeInterfaceDetails -> {tosca.interfaces.node.lifecycle.Standard={create={description=Standard lifecycle create operation.}, configure={description=Standard lifecycle configure operation.}, start={description=Standard lifecycle start operation.}, stop={description=Standard lifecycle stop operation.}, delete={description=Standard lifecycle delete operation.}}}\n\nI have UT coverage in corresponding SDC Parser APIs which will be raised for review once JTosca dependency goes in.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2125,
        "name": "Priyanshu Agarwal",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "pagarwal@amdocs.com",
        "username": "priyanshua"
      },
